article.description: Blake Kemp threw for two touchdowns and Griffin Roehler kicked four field goals as Northern Arizona topped Weber State 33-20 on Saturday.
article.headline: Northern Arizona tops Weber State 33-20
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Blake Kemp threw for two touchdowns and Griffin Roehler kicked four field goals as Northern Arizona topped Weber State 33-20 on Saturday. Kemp had 357 yards on 24 of 41 passing for the Lumberjacks (5-4, 4-2 Big Sky). Kendyl Taylor ran for 67 yards and a touchdown and caught a scoring pass. Joe Logan added 74 yards rushing. Kemp threw scoring passes to Taylor and William Morehand in the first half and Roehler kicked field goals of 25 and 36 yards to give Northern Arizona a 20-7 lead at halftime. Weber State cut Northern Arizona's lead to 26-20 with 5:47 left in the fourth quarter but two plays into the ensuing drive, Taylor ran for a 61-yard touchdown to stretch it to 33-20 with 5:14 to play. The Lumberjacks' Keith Graham intercepted Jadrian Clark with 1:23 remaining to seal with win. Clark threw for 302 yards and two touchdowns for the Wildcats (5-4, 4-2).
